o believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.504336, "shard": "02", "shelf_id": "sn83016689, 1910-12-13, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/mimtptc", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["detroit", "wayne county (mich.)", "michigan", "wayne", "newspapers", "wayne county", "united states", "detroit (mich.)"], "subject_headings": ["Detroit (Mich.)--Newspapers", "Wayne County (Mich.)--Newspapers", "Michigan--Detroit", "Michigan--Wayne County", "United States--Michigan--Wayne--Detroit"], "subjects": [{"detroit": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:detroit&fo=json"}, {"detroit (mich.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:detroit+%28mich.%29&fo=json"}, {"michigan": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:michigan&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"wayne": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne&fo=json"}, {"wayne county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne+county&fo=json"}, {"wayne county (mich.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne+county+%28mich.%29&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2024-01-17T10:32:19.003Z", "title": "The Detroit times (Detroit, Mich.), December 13, 1910, (FIRST EDITION)", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/1910-12-13/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83016689", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/6d68b9ef-1c0d-561a-ab92-9e08847758e0"], "batch": ["mimtptc_edenville_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1903", "description": ["Daily 3rd yr., no. 89 (Jan. 12, 1903)-21st yr., no. 50 (Nov. 27, 1920). Independent. Cf. Ayer, 1960. Publisher: W.E. Anderman, <1945>. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Detroit daily times (Detroit, Mich. : 1920) (DLC)sn 96076541 (OCoLC)34382991"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:08.284Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-10", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-10"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [42.3329407, -83.0478365], "location": ["detroit", "michigan", "wayne", "wayne county", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-83.0478365, 42.3329407], "number": ["1", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/1917-12-21/ed-2/", "original", "new york state libr", "2688-9390", "detroit public library", "boston athenaeum", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/1908-01-01/ed-1/", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "sn96076537", "library of congress", "2024-01-10t18:39:57.321128", "2025-07-01t13:41:00.400000", "library of michigan", "sn83016689", "4456", "sn96076541", "microfilm service copy", "9977557", "new york hist soc, newsp proj"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "the detroit times (detroit, mich.) 1903-1920"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 70.40905, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["detroit", "wayne county (mich.)", "michigan", "wayne", "newspapers", "wayne county", "united states", "detroit (mich.)"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:30:06.003Z", "title": "The Detroit times", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016689/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95070373/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn95070373", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/c46679b9-b94a-5fd9-b779-c272ac89c04e"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1995", "dates": ["[1995 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Daily Began July 13, 1995. Back issues available online. Print ed.: Detroit news (Detroit, Mich. : 1905). Mode of access: World Wide Web. Description based on: Aug. 18, 1995; title from title screen. Latest issue consulted: 145th year, No. 238 (April 17, 2019) (surrogate)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:34:05.793Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-03", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-03"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95070373/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["detroit", "michigan", "wayne", "wayne county", "united states"], "number": ["sn95070373", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "33115544", "2690-7186", "online resource", "2025-11-07t15:14:20.700000"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "catalog", "the detroit news ([detroit, mich.]) 1995-current [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 61.26442, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["detroit", "wayne county (mich.)", "michigan", "wayne", "periodicals", "newspapers", "wayne county", "united states", "electronic journals", "detroit (mich.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-27T08:50:05.467Z", "title": "The Detroit news", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95070373/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2019201736/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2019201736", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/a75bc0b9-b4b9-51ec-92f4-ab1f43e513f5"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1858", "dates": ["[1858 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Daily Print began with 1858. Issue for May 10, 1931 called: One hundredth anniversary edition. Editors: Wilbur F. Storey, Aug. 18, 1858-June 4, 1861; Henry N. Walker, June 5-Aug. 27, 1861. Due to strike on Apr. 15, 1962, combined with: Detroit news (Detroit, Mich. : 1905) and called: Detroit news-the Detroit free press. Due to a strike from July 15, 1995-Jan. 1, 1996, combined with: Detroit news (Detroit, Mich. : 1905) and called: Detroit news and free press. Saturday and Sunday issues combined with: Detroit news (Detroit, Mich. : 1905) and called: Detroit news and free press, Dec. 2, 1989-Apr. 30, 2006. Sunday issues include editorial page from Detroit news (Detroit, Mich. : 1905) and called: Sunday free press, May 7, 2006- Issue numbers v. 94, no. 120-v. 94, no. 265 skipped. Suspended Dec. 2, 1955-Jan. 16, 1956; Apr. 12-May 10, 1962; July 14-Nov. 24, 1964; Nov. 18, 1967-Aug. 9, 1968. Saturday and Sunday issues also have numbering for Detroit news. Other daily ed.: Detroit free press (Detroit, Mich. : State ed.). Weekly eds.: Detroit free press (Detroit, Mich. : Weekly), and; Detroit weekly free press; and: Weekly Detroit free press. Regional eds.: Weekly Detroit free press (Detroit, Mich. : Mich. ed.); Semiweekly ed.: Twice-a-week Detroit free press. Description based on: Volume 189, No. 64 (July 7, 2019); title from digital edition caption (freep.com, surrogate provided by publisher, viewed September 24, 2019). Latest issue consulted: Volume 189, No. 64 (July 7, 2019) (viewed September 24, 2019)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:01.189Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-15", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-15"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2019201736/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["detroit", "michigan", "wayne", "wayne county", "united states"], "number": ["2019201736", "2689-0410", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "137343179", "sn97063368", "online resource", "2025-11-07t12:37:05.400000"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Detroit news-the Detroit free press", "Detroit news and free press", "Sunday free press"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "detroit free press (detroit, mich.;detroit, michigan) 1858-current [online resource]", "catalog", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 61.26442, "shelf_id": "Newspapers", "site": ["usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["detroit", "wayne county (mich.)", "michigan", "wayne", "periodicals", "newspapers", "wayne county", "united states", "electronic journals", "detroit (mich.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:57:39.303Z", "title": "Detroit free press", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2019201736/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218642/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1933", "dates": ["[1933 TO 1933]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. XV, no. 21 (April 14, 1933); ceased with vol. XVI, no. 5 (Dec. 23, 1933). \"Independent.\" Cf. Ayer, 1967. \"Leading Negro weekly of Michigan.\" Merged with: Detroit independent, to form: Tribune independent of Michigan. Description based on: Vol. XV, no. 21 (April 14, 1933); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed March 14, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XVI, no. 5 (Dec. 23, 1933) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed March 14, 2018). Detroit independent Tribune independent of Michigan 2577-2570 (DLC) 2018218643 (OCoLC)1028674923"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:42.357Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218642/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["detroit", "michigan", "wayne", "wayne county", "united states"], "number": ["2577-2546", "2018218643", "1028641252", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2018218642", "online resource"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["detroit tribune (detroit, michigan) 1933-1933 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 61.26442, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["detroit", "wayne county (mich.)", "race relations", "michigan", "wayne", "newspapers", "wayne county", "united states", "african american", "african americans", "detroit (mich.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:56:09.337Z", "title": "Detroit tribune", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218642/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218643/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1933", "dates": ["[1933 TO 1935]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with [volume XI], no. 38 (December 30, 1933); ceased with volume XIII, no. 25 (Sept. 7, 1935). \"On guard for Negro rights.\" Publisher: Midwest Publishing Company, Inc., <December 29, 1934>-September 7, 1935. Also available on microfilm from Xerox University Microfilms. Formed by the union of: Detroit tribune (Detroit, Mich. : 1933), and: Detroit independent. Description based on: [Volume XI], no. 38 (December 30, 1933); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed M